-- Ghanaian Oil Exports to Start in January, Business & Financial Times Says
-- B y   J a s o n   M c L u r e
-- 2010-12-20T09:41:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-20/ghanaian-oil-exports-to-start-in-january-business-financial-times-says.html
Ghana  will start exporting oil from
its offshore Jubilee field in January, the  Business and
Financial Times  said, citing  Nana Asafu-Adjaye , chief executive
officer of the Ghana National Petroleum Corp.  The first shipment of 650,000 barrels of light sweet crude
will be marketed by oil trader Vitol Group, the Accra-based
newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Jason McLure  in Accra on 
 jmclure@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin in Johannesburg at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  